Build and Installation Instructions for Professor_AI
=====================================================

Prerequisites
-------------

Required:
  - C/C++ compiler with C11 support (GCC 7+ or Clang 5+)
  - CMake 3.14 or later
  - Internet connection (for FetchContent to download dependencies)
    OR local copies of llama.cpp, mongoose, and cJSON

Optional:
  - ROCm (for AMD GPU acceleration)
  - CUDA (for NVIDIA GPU acceleration)
  - libsystemd-dev (for sd_notify readiness signaling)


Building
--------

Standard build with AMD GPU (ROCm):

    cmake -B build -DGGML_HIP=ON -DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Release
    cmake --build build -j$(nproc)

With systemd readiness notification:

    cmake -B build -DGGML_HIP=ON -DPROF_USE_SYSTEMD=ON -DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Release
    cmake --build build -j$(nproc)

CPU-only build:

    cmake -B build -DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Release
    cmake --build build -j$(nproc)

NVIDIA GPU build (CUDA):

    cmake -B build -DGGML_CUDA=ON -DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Release
    cmake --build build -j$(nproc)

Debug build with tests:

    cmake -B build -DPROF_BUILD_TESTS=ON -DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Debug
    cmake --build build -j$(nproc)
    ctest --test-dir build --output-on-failure


Using Local Dependencies
------------------------

Each dependency can be overridden with a local path instead of
downloading via FetchContent:

    cmake -B build \
      -DLOCAL_LLAMA_PATH=/path/to/llama.cpp \
      -DLOCAL_MONGOOSE_PATH=/path/to/mongoose \
      -DLOCAL_CJSON_PATH=/path/to/cJSON \
      -DGGML_HIP=ON

This is useful for air-gapped builds or when working with modified
versions of a dependency.


Installation
------------

Install to /usr/local/bin (default):

    sudo cmake --install build

Install to a custom prefix:

    cmake -B build -DCMAKE_INSTALL_PREFIX=/opt/professord ...
    cmake --build build -j$(nproc)
    sudo cmake --install build

Copy the example config:

    sudo cp etc/professord.ini.example /etc/professord.ini
    sudo editor /etc/professord.ini    # set model_path at minimum


systemd Service
---------------

The service uses Type=notify -- professord signals readiness after
the model is fully loaded. This means systemctl start will not return
until the daemon is actually ready to serve requests (or fails).

1. Create a service user:

    sudo useradd -r -s /usr/sbin/nologin professord
    sudo usermod -aG video,render professord

2. Install the service file:

    sudo cp etc/professord.service /etc/systemd/system/
    sudo systemctl daemon-reload

3. Edit the config:

    sudo editor /etc/professord.ini

4. Start the service:

    sudo systemctl enable --now professord
    sudo systemctl status professord
    journalctl -u professord -f


Verifying the Build
-------------------

Run unit tests (if built with PROF_BUILD_TESTS=ON):

    ctest --test-dir build --output-on-failure

Check what models are recommended for your hardware:

    ./build/professord --recommend

Smoke test a running instance:

    curl -s http://localhost:8080/health

Quick integration test (requires a running instance with a loaded model):

    bash tests/test_curl.sh [base_url] [api_key]

Full test suite (unit + functional + stress + stability, generates report):

    bash tests/test_all.sh [base_url] [api_key]

Reports are written to tests/reports/report-YYYYMMDD-HHMMSS.md


Verifying ROCm Detection
-------------------------

After configuring with -DGGML_HIP=ON, check the CMake output for:

    -- Found hip
    -- HIP SDK version: ...

If these lines are absent, ROCm was not detected and llama.cpp will
build CPU-only. Ensure ROCm is installed and that the HIP compiler
(hipcc) is in your PATH.


Troubleshooting
---------------

"model_path is required":
    Set --model on the command line or model_path in the INI file.

Build fails downloading dependencies:
    Check internet connectivity, or use LOCAL_*_PATH options with
    locally cloned repositories.

GPU not detected at runtime:
    Ensure the user running professord is in the video and render
    groups. Check ROCm/CUDA installation with rocminfo or nvidia-smi.

Port already in use:
    Change listen_addr in config or via --listen-addr.

401 Unauthorized on all requests:
    If api_key is set in config, include -H "Authorization: Bearer <key>"
    in your curl commands. The /health endpoint does not require auth.

503 Server Busy:
    professord serves one inference at a time. Wait for the current
    request to complete or time out before sending another.

systemctl start hangs:
    The service uses Type=notify and waits for the model to load.
    Large models can take 30+ seconds. Check journalctl for progress.

No log output when daemonized:
    When running with --daemonize, logs go to syslog, not stderr.
    View with: journalctl -t professord -f
    Or use --log-file to write to a file in addition to syslog.

Too much console output:
    llama.cpp and mongoose debug messages are routed through the logger.
    Use --log-level 4 (ERROR) for quiet operation, or --log-level 2
    (INFO) for normal operation. Level 0 (TRACE) shows everything.

Low token throughput:
    LLM token generation is memory-bandwidth bound. Use --recommend to
    see estimated tok/s for different model sizes on your hardware.
    Smaller quantizations (Q3_K_M) and smaller models run faster.
    Ensure all layers are GPU-offloaded (n_gpu_layers >= model layers).

Performance tuning:
    --n-threads N    CPU threads for prompt processing (0 = auto)
    --n-batch N      Batch size for prompt eval (default 2048)
    n_threads=0 auto-detects to nproc/2 which is optimal for most systems.
